WEBVTT

00:01.120 --> 00:03.509
That was very nice, Mindy.

00:03.680 --> 00:04.954
Okay.

00:05.120 --> 00:07.236
Jake, we're ready to hear your report.

00:08.520 --> 00:11.557
- Jake?
- Just a sec.

00:12.160 --> 00:13.832
Now, Jake.

00:14.560 --> 00:18.155
Okay, I'm finished.

00:19.720 --> 00:23.235
- Does spelling and grammar count?
- It's an oral report, Jake.

00:23.400 --> 00:25.311
Oh, so it's like an oral thermometer.

00:25.480 --> 00:26.754
Right.

00:27.480 --> 00:29.391
Good thing it's not a rectal report.

00:31.080 --> 00:33.469
- Just read it.
- Okay.

00:34.040 --> 00:36.235
"My Weekend, by Jake Harper.

00:36.400 --> 00:38.391
Grade five, Mrs. Flanigan's class.

00:38.560 --> 00:41.438
Woodward Avenue Elementary School,
located on Woodward Avenue."

00:41.600 --> 00:42.953
I'm not counting words.

00:43.440 --> 00:45.670
Oh, good.

00:49.000 --> 00:52.390
"My weekend starts on Friday, when
my mom takes me to my dad's house.

00:52.560 --> 00:54.516
Which is actually
my Uncle Charlie's house.

00:54.680 --> 00:56.716
Who is my dad's brother,
making him my uncle.

00:56.880 --> 00:59.838
His name is Charlie, which is why
I call him my Uncle Charlie."

01:02.200 --> 01:03.918
Anyway...

01:04.080 --> 01:06.799
<i>"Even though my parents are divorced,</i>
<i>they still get along."</i>

01:06.960 --> 01:08.109
- Hey, buddy.
- Hey, Dad.

01:08.280 --> 01:09.759
- How was your week?
- Just fine.

01:09.920 --> 01:11.194
- Bye, honey.
- Bye, Mom.

01:11.360 --> 01:13.749
- Thanks for bringing him.
- Bite me. What the hell...

01:13.920 --> 01:16.388
...went on last weekend?
- What are you talking about?

01:16.560 --> 01:19.358
When I brought him home Sunday
night and served him dinner...

01:19.520 --> 01:22.114
...he tipped me with a $25 chip
from Caesars Palace...

01:22.280 --> 01:24.999
...and told me I had a nice rack.

01:26.160 --> 01:28.958
Well, Judith...

01:33.880 --> 01:35.677
...you do.

01:35.840 --> 01:37.592
That's not the point.

01:37.760 --> 01:40.479
Where'd he get the chip?
Where is he learning this behavior?

01:40.640 --> 01:42.631
Hey, Judith.

01:43.400 --> 01:45.356
Looking good.

01:45.920 --> 01:49.117
Run away, run away.

01:49.280 --> 01:52.113
Did you give my son a $25 chip?

01:52.280 --> 01:54.748
- No, I did not give him a $25 chip.
- Happy?

01:54.920 --> 01:57.753
He won it, fair and square.

01:58.400 --> 02:00.311
You couldn't run away.

02:00.480 --> 02:02.232
I don't care what you do on weekdays.

02:02.400 --> 02:05.710
But on weekends, remember you are
a role model for an 11 -year-old boy.

02:05.880 --> 02:09.475
Oh, that's a bad idea.
Who thought of that?

02:09.639 --> 02:13.679
I'm warning you. Things had better
change or there will be consequences.

02:13.840 --> 02:16.308
Legal consequences. Got it?

02:16.880 --> 02:19.110
- Got it.
- Goodbye.

02:23.720 --> 02:27.269
"There will be serious consequences.

02:27.440 --> 02:30.352
Legal consequences."

02:30.520 --> 02:33.796
"I don't care what you do
during the week.

02:34.560 --> 02:37.279
But on the weekends,
you're a role model."

02:38.760 --> 02:40.318
